u003eThese apps aren\u0026#39;t using some technical wizardry to trick you either. They\u0026#39;re originally phishing websites that have been converted to Android apps using the Median framework and distributed on the Play Store using developer accounts that were originally offering legitimate apps. Some apps skip the framework and load the phishing website directly in Android WebView.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n    \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"1f14-4854-acb057003dcd\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/tips-to-keep-android-phone-secure/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-hand-holding-android-phone-with-lock-and-secure-icon-in-background.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-hand-holding-android-phone-with-lock-and-secure-icon-in-background.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-hand-holding-android-phone-with-lock-and-secure-icon-in-background.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-hand-holding-android-phone-with-lock-and-secure-icon-in-background.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-hand-holding-android-phone-with-lock-and-secure-icon-in-background.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-hand-holding-android-phone-with-lock-and-secure-icon-in-background.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-hand-holding-android-phone-with-lock-and-secure-icon-in-background.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-hand-holding-android-phone-with-lock-and-secure-icon-in-background.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-hand-holding-android-phone-with-lock-and-secure-icon-in-background.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                    \u003cimg width=\"2100\" height=\"1400\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A hand holding Android phone with lock and secure icon in background\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-hand-holding-android-phone-with-lock-and-secure-icon-in-background.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-hand-holding-android-phone-with-lock-and-secure-icon-in-background.jpg\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n        \n                            \n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSome of these developer accounts have as many as 100,000 downloads. Researchers believe that these are older developer accounts that were compromised and are now being used to deliver these phishing apps instead.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eOnce you see the phishing website, which impersonates a legitimate wallet, you\u0026#39;re asked to enter your 12-word mnemonic phrase. As soon as you do that, you\u0026#39;ve handed the keys to your crypto wallet to the hackers.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"keep-your-wallet-close-and-your-codes-closer\"\u003e\n                        Keep Your Wallet Close, and Your Codes Closer\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThis campaign is another reminder that you should always check app reviews and descriptions before downloading them, even if you\u0026#39;re on the official app store for your platform. When dealing with crypto apps, check to ensure you\u0026#39;re downloading the app from the official developer, and not an impostor.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n    \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"9a27-420a-a3f4b53f40b2\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/what-do-if-crypto-wallet-hacked/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/crypto-wallet-pic-1.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;Image Credit: \u0026lt;a href=\\\u0026#34;https:\\/\\/www.quoteinspector.com\\/images\\/bitcoin\\/bitcoins-protruding-wallet\\/\\\u0026#34; rel=\\\u0026#34;noopener noreferrer\\\u0026#34; target=\\\u0026#34;_blank\\\u0026#34;\u0026gt;QuoteInspector\u0026lt;\\/a\u0026gt;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/crypto-wallet-pic-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/crypto-wallet-pic-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/crypto-wallet-pic-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/crypto-wallet-pic-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/crypto-wallet-pic-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/crypto-wallet-pic-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/crypto-wallet-pic-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/crypto-wallet-pic-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                    \u003cimg width=\"1680\" height=\"840\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"cryptocurrency bitcoin next to wallet\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/crypto-wallet-pic-1.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/crypto-wallet-pic-1.jpg\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\n                \n                 \n                \t\n\u003ch5\u003e\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t        \t\t\t\t\n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/what-do-if-crypto-wallet-hacked/\" title=\"What to Do If Your Crypto Wallet Gets Hacked\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\n\t\t\tWhat to Do If Your Crypto Wallet Gets Hacked\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\u003c/h5\u003e\n\n                                                    \n                \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eCrypto wallets aren\u0026#39;t impervious to attack—they\u0026#39;re a prime target. So, what do you do if your crypto wallet gets hacked?\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\n                    \n\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n                \t\n\n\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eKeep in mind that legitimate crypto services will never ask for your mnemonic phrase unless you manually try to recover your account. If you\u0026#39;re asked for a mnemonic phrase during usual logins, something is off. In such cases, immediately check the site URL, and if it\u0026#39;s anything but the legitimate site, it\u0026#39;s time to close that tab immediately.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                                            \n\n    \n\n\n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
